This will fix the symptoms, but the problem is actually that there  
should be a file display.m in @ThermoPhase that isn&#39;t there in the  
Windows binary distribution.  It is supposed to be missing from  
@Solution, so that it inherits this method from @ThermoPhase, but since  
that file was left out, there is nothing to inherit. This was fixed in  
the latest Windows installer, so I would recommend downloading and  
running Cantera160r1.msi.  Since a few other problems were fixed in  
this version, too, I recommend that everyone using Cantera on Windows  
install this latest version, unless you are building Cantera from  
source code.

Dave


